<title>USA: Philip Morris may issue $500 mln in debt.</title>
<headline>Philip Morris may issue $500 mln in debt.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Philip Morris Cos Inc is expected to tap the corporate bond new issue market with a $500 million debt offering, syndicate sources said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>The A2/A rated deal is expected to consist of a seven-year maturity with Goldman Sachs &amp; Co acting as lead underwriter for the offering, sources said.</p>
<p>The deal may price as early as Wednesday, they addes.</p>
<p>(( --Nancy Leinfuss, 212-859-1675 ))</p>
